Dispersion parameter \(\phi = 38.06172\) which can be calculated based on m1 model:

pearson_r <- residuals(m1, type = "pearson")
sum(pearson_r^2)/m1$df.residual
[1] 38.06172

This means that the variance of residuals is 37 times larger than the mean, and thus we should adjust standard errors by 6.169418. So, lets check and compare standard errors from m2 with those from m1.

summary(summary(m2)$coef[,2]/summary(m1)$coef[,2])
   Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
  6.169   6.169   6.169   6.169   6.169   6.169

Interpretation:

  • if the company size decreases from big to medium (ceteris paribus) then average number of vacancies decrease by 86% (1- 0.14).
  • if we compare companies from dolnoÅlÄskie (02) with mazowieckie (14, woj14; ceteris paribus) then average number of vacancies will increase by 80%.
